// Content Sprint 5: Marketplace Structure.
window.CONTENT_SPRINT_5 = {"understanding-taxonomy":{"summary":"Understand how Categories, Prototypes, Option Types, Option Values and Brands work together to create a consistent product structure for Seller onboarding, product mapping, connected systems and catalogue operations.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller management","Ecommerce","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understanding Marketplace Taxonomy":"\n<p>A taxonomy is the marketplace structure used to classify and describe products. It determines where an Advert belongs, which product attributes Sellers complete, which customer selections create Variants and how Seller data is standardised.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use one marketplace language.</strong> Sellers may use different Categories, Brands and attribute labels in their own systems. Map those source values into one approved Marketplacer structure.</div>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Category</td><td>Places the Advert in the hierarchy</td><td>Electronics > Video > Computer Monitors</td></tr><tr><td>Prototype</td><td>Groups the attributes used by a product type</td><td>Computer Monitors</td></tr><tr><td>Advert Option Type</td><td>Describes the overall Advert</td><td>Display Resolution</td></tr><tr><td>Variant Option Type</td><td>Distinguishes a purchasable Variant</td><td>Colour</td></tr><tr><td>Option Value</td><td>Provides an approved controlled value</td><td>Black</td></tr><tr><td>Brand</td><td>Identifies the product Brand</td><td>Samsung</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Taxonomy supports product creation, bulk spreadsheets, mapping, filters, Catalog Rules, tax, commission, reporting and connected ecommerce experiences.</p>\n","Taxonomy Components":"\n<h3>Categories</h3><p>Categories place Adverts within a hierarchy. Guide Sellers to the most specific appropriate product Category where one exists.</p>\n<h3>Prototypes</h3><p>A Prototype is a reusable template containing the Advert, Variant and supported free-text fields required for one or more Categories.</p>\n<h3>Option Types and Option Values</h3><p>Option Types define the attribute being collected. Option Values provide the controlled answers Sellers can select or map.</p>\n<h3>Brands</h3><p>Brands are shared marketplace records managed by the Operator. Keep Seller identity separate from product Brand identity.</p>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Design the components together.</strong> A Category name may look correct while its Prototype, Variant structure or controlled values still require work.</div>\n","How Categories and Attributes Work Together":"\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Category selected</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Assigned Prototype loaded</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Advert and Variant Option Types displayed</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Option Values selected or mapped</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Advert and Variants created</strong></div></div>\n<p>For example, <code>Electronics > Video > Computer Monitors</code> may use a <code>Computer Monitors</code> Prototype containing Display Resolution, Display Technology and Device Interface as Advert Option Types, with Colour as a Variant Option Type.</p>\n<h3>Reuse Prototypes deliberately</h3><p>Several Categories can share one Prototype where their product-data requirements are genuinely the same. Create a separate Prototype when the attributes, compliance information or customer selections differ materially.</p>\n<h3>Grouping Categories</h3><p>Use an approved blank or minimal Prototype for parent and intermediate Categories that organise the hierarchy but are not intended to receive products directly.</p>\n","Backend Taxonomy and Front-End Navigation":"\n<p>The Marketplacer taxonomy does not need to duplicate the customer-facing website menu.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Marketplacer taxonomy</th><th>Customer-facing ecommerce</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller product classification</td><td>Navigation menus</td></tr><tr><td>Prototypes and product attributes</td><td>Collections and landing pages</td></tr><tr><td>Variant structure</td><td>Campaign and editorial groupings</td></tr><tr><td>Tax, commission and Catalog Rules</td><td>Search presentation and merchandising</td></tr><tr><td>Operational reporting</td><td>Customer-facing labels</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>A stable backend Category such as <code>Dog Food</code> can support front-end Collections such as Dry Dog Food, Wet Dog Food and Puppy Food using attributes including Pet Food Form and Dog Age Group.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Do not design from the website menu alone.</strong> The taxonomy also needs to support Seller mapping, product data, integrations, finance rules and reporting.</div>\n","Standardisation and Seller Mapping":"\n<p>Mapping translates Seller source values into the marketplace standard.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller source</th><th>Marketplace value</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Technology > Displays</td><td>Electronics > Video > Computer Monitors</td></tr><tr><td>Samsung Electronics</td><td>Samsung</td></tr><tr><td>Screen Resolution</td><td>Display Resolution</td></tr><tr><td>Charcoal</td><td>Grey</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Once an approved mapping is created for a Seller source value, it can be reused for later imports from that Seller.</p>\n<h3>Prefer mapping to duplicate values</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Map alternate spelling and capitalisation</li><li>Map Seller terminology and abbreviations</li><li>Map marketing colour names to useful controlled values</li><li>Create a new marketplace value only when it represents a meaningful distinction</li></ul>\n<h3>Maintain controlled values</h3><p>Use one standard for units, capitalisation and terminology so bulk files, integrations, filters and reports remain predictable.</p>\n","Taxonomy Design Decisions":"\n<h3>Confirm the product scope</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Launch product families</li><li>Near-term expansion</li><li>Restricted or regulated products</li><li>Physical, digital or service products</li><li>Seller source systems</li></ul>\n<h3>Separate descriptive and customer-selectable data</h3><p>Use an Advert Option Type when the value describes the overall product. Use a Variant Option Type when the customer selects the value while purchasing.</p>\n<h3>Use Categories for product types</h3><p>Create another Category when it represents a meaningful product type, requires another Prototype or supports a material operational rule. Use attributes or front-end Collections for filters, campaigns and temporary ranges.</p>\n<h3>Review dependencies</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Front-end filters and product pages</li><li>Commission Package Category rules</li><li>Category tax overrides</li><li>Catalog Rules and Product Vetting</li><li>Integration and reporting requirements</li></ul>\n","Change Management and Governance":"\n<p>Assign a named Operator owner for Categories, Prototypes, Option Types, Option Values and Brands. Sellers map to the marketplace structure rather than creating uncontrolled taxonomy records.</p>\n<h3>New value request process</h3><ol><li>Review the Seller product and source value.</li><li>Search the existing marketplace structure.</li><li>Confirm whether mapping resolves the request.</li><li>Review front-end, integration, tax, commission and Catalog Rule impact.</li><li>Approve or decline the new value.</li><li>Update mappings and test the product.</li><li>Record the decision.</li></ol>\n<h3>Live changes</h3><p>Before changing a live Category, Prototype or controlled value, identify affected products, Sellers, mappings, integrations, filters and financial rules. Test the migration in Sandbox before applying it in Production.</p>\n","Readiness and Validation":"\n<p>Validate the structure using representative Seller products before onboarding the full catalogue.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Test area</th><th>Confirm</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Classification</td><td>Correct Category and hierarchy depth</td></tr><tr><td>Product fields</td><td>Correct Prototype and Advert attributes</td></tr><tr><td>Variants</td><td>Customer-selectable values create unique combinations</td></tr><tr><td>Controlled data</td><td>Approved Option Values and Brand</td></tr><tr><td>Seller onboarding</td><td>Manual, bulk and integrated workflows</td></tr><tr><td>Connected systems</td><td>Front-end display, filters and reporting</td></tr><tr><td>Governance</td><td>Tax, commission, Catalog Rules and Product Vetting</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Readiness checklist</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Launch scope and ownership approved</li><li>Representative Seller data reviewed</li><li>Category and Prototype relationships validated</li><li>Advert and Variant attributes separated correctly</li><li>Mapping and new-value processes documented</li><li>Sandbox and Production alignment planned</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/27901303371533-Marketplacer-Global-Taxonomy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Marketplacer Global Taxonomy</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952526071949-Create-a-prototype\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create a Prototype</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952568064013-Add-a-prototype-to-a-category\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Add a Prototype to a Category</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952355396749-Add-option-values-to-variants-or-features\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Add Option Values to Variants or Features</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31709387005709-Updating-categories-and-prototypes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Updating Categories and Prototypes</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["global-taxonomy","Global Taxonomy"],["option-types","Option Types"],["setup-sequence","Recommended Setup Sequence"]]},"global-taxonomy":{"summary":"Use the Marketplacer Global Taxonomy as a standard starting point for Categories, Prototypes, Option Types and Option Values, then apply targeted changes for your launch range and operating model.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller management","Ecommerce","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understanding the Global Taxonomy":"\n<p>The Marketplacer Global Taxonomy provides a standardised product-classification and attribute framework aligned with recognised ecommerce structures. It can reduce the work required to build Categories, Prototypes, Option Types and Option Values from the beginning.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use it as a baseline.</strong> You still decide which Categories support your launch range, which attributes are required and how the structure maps to your front end and Seller data.</div>\n<p>After adoption, the components are managed through the standard menus:</p><p><code>Categorisation &gt; Option Types | Prototypes | Categories | Brands</code></p>\n","Benefits of Starting with the Global Taxonomy":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Benefit</th><th>Operational value</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Faster setup</td><td>Begin with a broad reference structure rather than creating every component</td></tr><tr><td>Seller familiarity</td><td>Common ecommerce classifications can reduce mapping effort</td></tr><tr><td>Consistent data</td><td>One standard improves filters, reports and catalogue governance</td></tr><tr><td>Integration readiness</td><td>Stable Categories and attributes reduce Seller-specific transformations</td></tr><tr><td>Scalable expansion</td><td>Adjacent product families can be added within the same framework</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Alignment with other taxonomies improves mapping but does not mean every Category name or identifier will match another system exactly.</p>\n","Reviewing the Reference Taxonomy":"\n<p>Review the reference against representative launch products rather than approving Category names in isolation.</p>\n<h3>Collect</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Seller Category paths</li><li>Product titles and Brands</li><li>Advert attributes</li><li>Variant options and values</li><li>Product source systems</li><li>Expected launch volume</li></ul>\n<h3>Review each product family</h3><ol><li>Identify the proposed Global Taxonomy path.</li><li>Confirm the Category receives products directly or only groups child Categories.</li><li>Review the assigned Prototype.</li><li>Check the Advert and Variant attributes.</li><li>Record missing or unnecessary fields.</li><li>Confirm front-end and integration use.</li></ol>\n","Choosing Categories for Launch":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Approach</th><th>Use when</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Complete Global Taxonomy</td><td>The marketplace expects broad and frequent range expansion</td></tr><tr><td>Approved subset</td><td>Launch scope is defined and a focused Seller experience is preferred</td></tr><tr><td>Standard plus targeted additions</td><td>Most product types fit but specialist gaps remain</td></tr><tr><td>Custom structure informed by the standard</td><td>Industry or regulatory classifications require another hierarchy</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Guide Sellers to the most specific appropriate Category. Keep customer filters such as colour, food form or age group as attributes when they do not represent separate operational product types.</p>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Separate launch and future scope.</strong> Use statuses such as Launch, Near-term, Future, Not applicable and Requires review.</div>\n","Adapting the Global Taxonomy":"\n<p>Make targeted changes where they improve the marketplace product model.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Add a missing specialist Category</li><li>Add a marketplace-specific Prototype</li><li>Add an Advert or Variant Option Type</li><li>Add approved Option Values</li><li>Adjust optionality or search use</li><li>Add local tax codes or alternative search terms</li></ul>\n<h3>Before creating a custom Category</h3><ol><li>Check whether an existing Category applies.</li><li>Check whether an attribute can represent the distinction.</li><li>Confirm a separate Prototype, tax rule or reporting class is required.</li><li>Review Seller mapping and front-end impact.</li></ol>\n<p>Record every deviation from the standard, its reason, owner and affected systems.</p>\n","Implementing in Sandbox and Production":"\n<p>Agree with your Marketplacer Delivery Manager whether the approved structure will be imported, created manually, uploaded in bulk or managed through API workflows.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Option Types</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Option Values</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Prototypes</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Categories</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Brands</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Seller mapping</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Product testing</strong></div></div>\n<p>Create and validate the structure in Sandbox first. Compare component counts, hierarchy, Prototype assignments, Option Values, Brands, tax settings and custom additions before applying the approved result in Production.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Verify every import.</strong> Confirm the resulting structure in both environments rather than assuming the files produced identical outcomes.</div>\n","Seller Mapping and Product Onboarding":"\n<p>The adopted taxonomy becomes the standard into which each Seller maps its source data.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller source</th><th>Marketplace standard</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Pet Supplies > Food > Dog Meals</td><td>Animals & Pet Supplies > Pet Supplies > Dog Supplies > Dog Food</td></tr><tr><td>Samsung Electronics</td><td>Samsung</td></tr><tr><td>Screen Resolution</td><td>Display Resolution</td></tr><tr><td>Charcoal</td><td>Grey</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Test manual product creation, V2 bulk spreadsheets, MConnect or API product imports, Category mapping, Brand mapping and Option Value mapping using representative launch Sellers.</p>\n<h3>Seller resources</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Approved Category scope</li><li>Attribute definitions</li><li>Variant rules</li><li>Brand standards</li><li>Mapping instructions</li><li>New-value request process</li></ul>\n","Governance and Expansion":"\n<p>Treat the adopted Global Taxonomy as a governed marketplace standard.</p>\n<h3>For each new range</h3><ol><li>Review the existing Category path.</li><li>Confirm the Prototype and attributes.</li><li>Add approved gaps.</li><li>Test Seller mapping and product templates.</li><li>Review front-end, tax, commission and Catalog Rule dependencies.</li><li>Approve the range for onboarding.</li></ol>\n<h3>Monitor quality</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Products in broad parent Categories</li><li>Product Categories using a blank Prototype</li><li>Duplicate Categories and attributes</li><li>Frequent mapping skips</li><li>Missing filter data</li><li>Unused Categories and values</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/27901303371533-Marketplacer-Global-Taxonomy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Marketplacer Global Taxonomy</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115007259468-How-to-set-up-your-categories\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How to Set Up Your Categories</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952526071949-Create-a-prototype\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create a Prototype</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952568064013-Add-a-prototype-to-a-category\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Add a Prototype to a Category</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003511551-Map-product-categories-brands-features-and-variants\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Map Product Categories, Brands, Features and Variants</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31709387005709-Updating-categories-and-prototypes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Updating Categories and Prototypes</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["understanding-taxonomy","Understanding Taxonomy"],["categories","Categories"],["mapping","Mapping"]]},"option-types":{"summary":"Define the reusable product attributes Sellers complete, using Advert Option Types for the overall Advert and Variant Option Types for customer-selectable differences between purchasable Variants.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller management","Ecommerce","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understanding Option Types":"\n<p>Option Types are reusable product attributes associated with an Advert or Variant. They determine which fields appear during product creation, bulk uploads, mapping and connected product onboarding.</p>\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Option Types</code></p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Option Type</td><td>Colour</td></tr><tr><td>Option Value</td><td>Black</td></tr><tr><td>Prototype</td><td>T-Shirts</td></tr><tr><td>Category</td><td>Clothing > T-Shirts</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Create Option Types first, add their controlled Option Values, then group the attributes into Prototypes.</p>\n","Advert and Variant Option Types":"\n<h3>Advert Option Type</h3><p>Use for information describing the overall product, such as Material, Display Resolution, Product Form, Compatibility or Dietary Preference.</p>\n<h3>Variant Option Type</h3><p>Use for a customer-selectable difference between purchasable Variants, such as Colour, Size, Pack Quantity or Storage Capacity.</p>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Use the customer-selection test.</strong> Does the value describe the product, or must the customer select it when purchasing?</div>\n<p>Each Variant should have a unique combination of Variant Option Values. Keep the Variant structure focused on genuine purchase choices.</p>\n","Planning Option Types":"\n<p>Design Option Types from representative Seller products and the intended customer experience.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller field</th><th>Marketplace treatment</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Screen Resolution</td><td>Advert Option Type: Display Resolution</td></tr><tr><td>Colour</td><td>Variant Option Type: Colour</td></tr><tr><td>Charcoal</td><td>Map to Option Value: Grey</td></tr><tr><td>Manufacturer Part Number</td><td>Standard Variant field</td></tr><tr><td>Campaign Name</td><td>Front-end Collection, not an Option Type</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Before creating one</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Confirm the business purpose</li><li>Search for an existing equivalent</li><li>Confirm Advert or Variant use</li><li>Choose controlled values or free text</li><li>Confirm front-end and integration destination</li><li>Confirm required or optional status</li></ul>\n","Creating an Option Type":"\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Option Types &gt; Create New Option Type</code></p>\n<ol><li>Select Advert or Variant in the applicable field.</li><li>Enter a clear internal Name.</li><li>Enter a concise Presentation label.</li><li>Select the closest Kind, such as Colour, Size or Other.</li><li>Add a Description that tells Sellers what to provide.</li><li>Select the supported input behaviour.</li><li>Save, then add Option Values where controlled data is required.</li></ol>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Name</td><td>Dog Kennel Material</td></tr><tr><td>Presentation</td><td>Material</td></tr><tr><td>Applies to</td><td>Advert</td></tr><tr><td>Kind</td><td>Other</td></tr><tr><td>Description</td><td>Select the primary external construction material.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Add the completed Option Type to the required Prototype and test it through Seller product creation.</p>\n","Required, Optional and Search Behaviour":"\n<p>Use required fields for information essential to customer choice, compliance, integration or catalogue governance. Use optional fields for useful enrichment that is not needed for every product.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Review live impact.</strong> Changing an optional Option Type to required can unpublish affected products until Sellers complete the required data.</div>\n<h3>Search and filter use</h3><p>Where supported, enable search behaviour only for attributes that help customers narrow products, such as Size, Colour, Material or Compatibility. Connected front ends may consume the same data while configuring filters independently.</p>\n<h3>Multi-value Advert attributes</h3><p>An Advert Option Type can support several values where the product has multiple compatible systems, dietary preferences or other descriptive characteristics.</p>\n","Free Text and Controlled Inputs":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Input</th><th>Use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Controlled Option Values</td><td>Mapping, filters, validation, reporting and consistent integrations</td></tr><tr><td>Free text</td><td>Highly specific descriptive information that does not need controlled mapping</td></tr><tr><td>Dropdown</td><td>A controlled Advert attribute that does not create a Variant</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Prefer controlled values when a stable list exists. Define approved units and formatting for measurements.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Avoid uncontrolled duplication.</strong> A controlled Pet Food Form field with Dry, Wet and Frozen is more reliable than free-text entries such as dry food, Kibble and DRY.</div>\n","Bulk Creation and Seller Mapping":"\n<p>Use <code>Categorisation &gt; Option Types &gt; Bulk Upload Option Types</code>, followed by <code>Bulk Upload Option Values</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Option Types</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Option Values</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Prototypes</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Categories</strong></div></div>\n<p>Validate duplicate names, Advert and Variant use, optionality, descriptions, input type and capitalisation before upload.</p>\n<h3>Seller mapping</h3><p>Map source fields such as Screen Resolution to Display Resolution and source values such as M to Medium. Seller mappings are specific to the Seller and environment, so maintain controlled records where they need to be recreated.</p>\n","Testing and Governance":"\n<p>Test the complete chain:</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Option Type created</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Option Values added</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Added to Prototype</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Prototype assigned to Category</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Manual and bulk product tested</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Front-end and integration checked</strong></div></div>\n<h3>Confirm</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Presentation and Description are clear</li><li>Required or optional status is correct</li><li>Advert fields apply to the whole product</li><li>Variant fields create unique combinations</li><li>V2 Multi Sheet and Single Sheet workflows behave as expected</li><li>Mappings, filters and connected data are correct</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21949682230285-Create-variants-or-features\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create Variants or Features</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952041077389-Fields-in-setting-up-new-option-types\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Fields in Setting Up New Option Types</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/14556672200205-Manage-optional-option-types\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Optional Option Types</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952355396749-Add-option-values-to-variants-or-features\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Add Option Values to Variants or Features</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360045774392-Filter-feature-option-types\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Filter Feature Option Types</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952526071949-Create-a-prototype\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create a Prototype</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["option-values","Option Values"],["prototypes","Prototypes"],["product-model","Product Model"]]},"option-values":{"summary":"Create and maintain the controlled values Sellers select for Advert and Variant Option Types so product data can be mapped, filtered, compared and reported consistently.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller management","Ecommerce","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understanding Option Values":"\n<p>An Option Value is a predefined answer available for an Option Type.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Option Type</th><th>Option Values</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Colour</td><td>Black, Blue, Grey, White</td></tr><tr><td>Display Resolution</td><td>1920 x 1080, 2560 x 1440</td></tr><tr><td>Dog Age Group</td><td>Puppy, Junior, Adult, Senior</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Advert Option Values describe the overall Advert. Variant Option Values identify customer-selectable Variant choices.</p>\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Option Types &gt; select the Option Type</code></p>\n","Planning Controlled Values":"\n<p>Create marketplace values from a controlled product standard rather than copying every Seller value.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller source</th><th>Treatment</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Charcoal</td><td>Map to Grey</td></tr><tr><td>Dark Grey</td><td>Map to Grey or retain where useful</td></tr><tr><td>Midnight Black</td><td>Map to Black</td></tr><tr><td>Custom marketing colour</td><td>Retain in description and map to the closest controlled colour</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Create a distinct value when it supports</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Customer selection</li><li>Useful filtering</li><li>Pricing or fulfilment</li><li>Compliance</li><li>Integration or reporting</li></ul>\n<p>Avoid values that duplicate the Option Type or combine several attributes into one value.</p>\n","Naming and Presentation":"\n<p>Use a stable Name and an equivalent user-facing Presentation.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Name</th><th>Presentation</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Extra Large</td><td>XL</td></tr><tr><td>United Kingdom Size 10</td><td>UK 10</td></tr><tr><td>Dark Grey</td><td>Dark Grey</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Use approved Brand and regional spelling</li><li>Apply consistent capitalisation</li><li>Use recognised abbreviations carefully</li><li>Use one unit format</li><li>Avoid Seller-specific prefixes</li></ul>\n<p>Exact spelling, spacing and capitalisation are important in bulk files and integrations that do not provide dropdowns.</p>\n","Creating and Ordering Values":"\n<ol><li>Open <code>Categorisation &gt; Option Types</code>.</li><li>Select the Option Type.</li><li>Select <strong>Add Option Value</strong>.</li><li>Enter Name and Presentation.</li><li>Save the value.</li><li>Arrange values in the intended order.</li><li>Update the Option Type.</li></ol>\n<h3>Use a logical order</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Natural sequence: XS, S, M, L, XL</li><li>Numeric sequence: 100 ml, 250 ml, 500 ml, 1 L</li><li>Life stage: Puppy, Junior, Adult, Senior</li><li>Alphabetical where no natural sequence applies</li></ul>\n<p>Before renaming or deleting a live value, identify products, Seller mappings, integrations, filters and Catalog Rules that depend on it.</p>\n","Advert, Variant and Multi-Select Values":"\n<h3>Advert values</h3><p>Use one or several values to describe the same Advert, such as Grain Free, Natural and Veterinarian Recommended.</p>\n<h3>Variant values</h3><p>Assign one clear value per Variant Option Type to each Variant. Create separate Variants where the customer can choose different values.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Variant</th><th>Colour</th><th>Size</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>Black</td><td>Small</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>Black</td><td>Medium</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>White</td><td>Small</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>White</td><td>Medium</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Each Variant should have a unique value combination. Do not use an Option Value to compensate for an incorrectly designed Option Type.</p>\n","Bulk Creation and Product Spreadsheets":"\n<p>Use <code>Categorisation &gt; Option Types &gt; Bulk Upload Option Values</code> after the Option Types exist.</p>\n<h3>V2 product workbooks</h3>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Format</th><th>Use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Multi Sheet</td><td>Category-based creation and enrichment with controlled dropdowns</td></tr><tr><td>Single Sheet</td><td>High-volume catalogue creation and updates in one table using the Data sheet as reference</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Blank cells leave existing values unchanged during supported updates</li><li><code>DELETE_VALUE</code> clears a supported optional field</li><li><code>DELETE_VALUE</code> is case-sensitive</li><li>Mandatory fields must remain populated</li><li>Use pipe-separated values only where the generated template supports multi-select</li></ul>\n","Seller Mapping and New Value Requests":"\n<p>Map Seller synonyms and formatting differences into one marketplace value.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Source</th><th>Marketplace</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Gray</td><td>Grey</td></tr><tr><td>XX-Large</td><td>XXL</td></tr><tr><td>1000 grams</td><td>1 kg</td></tr><tr><td>Kibble</td><td>Dry</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>New-value request</h3><ol><li>Collect the product, Option Type and requested source value.</li><li>Check for an existing equivalent.</li><li>Confirm whether mapping resolves it.</li><li>Assess customer, integration and reporting value.</li><li>Add and order the value where approved.</li><li>Update mapping and verify the affected product.</li></ol>\n","Testing and Governance":"\n<p>Test controlled values through manual product creation, V2 spreadsheets, Seller mapping, integrations and the connected front end.</p>\n<h3>Quality checks</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Duplicates and alternate spelling</li><li>Inconsistent capitalisation and units</li><li>Values under the wrong Option Type</li><li>Unused or excessively detailed values</li><li>Invalid Variant combinations</li><li>Fragmented customer filters</li></ul>\n<h3>Live change process</h3><p>Select the replacement value, update products and mappings in Sandbox, validate connected systems, then apply the approved Production migration.</p>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952355396749-Add-option-values-to-variants-or-features\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Add Option Values to Variants or Features</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21949682230285-Create-variants-or-features\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create Variants or Features</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952041077389-Fields-in-setting-up-new-option-types\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Fields in Setting Up New Option Types</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/34159145753869-How-to-manage-products-and-variants-in-bulk-multi-sheet\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Products and Variants in Bulk, Multi Sheet</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/41580919800077-How-to-manage-products-and-variants-in-bulk-single-sheet\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Products and Variants in Bulk, Single Sheet</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4414397900941-Marketplacer-glossary\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Marketplacer Glossary</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["option-types","Option Types"],["mapping","Mapping"],["bulk-product-management","Bulk Product Management"]]},"prototypes":{"summary":"Group the Advert, Variant and supported free-text attributes required for a product type into a reusable Prototype, then assign it to the appropriate Categories.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller management","Ecommerce","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understanding Prototypes":"\n<p>A Prototype is a reusable product template containing the attributes associated with one or more Categories.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Option Types and Values</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Prototype</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Category</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Seller product fields</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Advert and Variants</strong></div></div>\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Prototypes</code></p>\n<p>One Prototype can be reused across Categories that share the same product-data requirements. A suitable Prototype gives Seller source attributes a structured marketplace destination.</p>\n","Planning a Prototype":"\n<p>Begin with representative products and identify the information required to describe, compare, sell and govern the product type.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Product information</th><th>Treatment</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Construction material</td><td>Advert Option Type</td></tr><tr><td>Weather resistance</td><td>Advert Option Type</td></tr><tr><td>Kennel size</td><td>Variant Option Type</td></tr><tr><td>Seller SKU</td><td>Standard Variant field</td></tr><tr><td>Assembly notes</td><td>Free-text field or description</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Confirm customer and compliance requirements</li><li>Review Seller source data</li><li>Review front-end and integration fields</li><li>Search for an existing reusable Prototype</li><li>Keep unrelated attributes out of the template</li></ul>\n","Building the Attribute Set":"\n<h3>Advert Option Types</h3><p>Add information that applies to the overall product, such as Material, Product Form or Compatibility.</p>\n<h3>Variant Option Types</h3><p>Add the customer selections that distinguish purchasable Variants, such as Colour, Size or Pack Quantity.</p>\n<h3>Supported free-text fields</h3><p>Use for product-specific descriptive information where a controlled value list is impractical.</p>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Keep the Variant structure manageable.</strong> Add only the customer choices required to distinguish the purchasable items.</div>\n<p>Review the Option Values and required or optional behaviour before adding an Option Type to several Prototypes.</p>\n","Creating a Prototype":"\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Prototypes &gt; Create Prototype</code></p>\n<ol><li>Enter a clear product-type or reusable template name.</li><li>Create the Prototype.</li><li>Add the required Advert Option Types.</li><li>Add the required Variant Option Types.</li><li>Add supported free-text or dropdown fields.</li><li>Save the completed Prototype.</li><li>Assign it to the appropriate Categories.</li><li>Test a representative Seller product.</li></ol>\n<p>Create Option Types and Option Values before the Prototype so every required attribute is available during setup.</p>\n","Assigning Prototypes to Categories":"\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Categories &gt; edit Category &gt; Prototype</code></p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Category type</th><th>Prototype approach</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Product Category</td><td>Functional product-specific or approved shared Prototype</td></tr><tr><td>Parent or grouping Category</td><td>Blank Default, No Prototype or approved minimal Prototype</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Guide Sellers to the specific product Category that supplies the correct Prototype. A broad parent Category can produce weak product data and irrelevant fields.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Assign every Category deliberately.</strong> Keep grouping Categories structurally complete while preventing products from being assigned to an empty product model.</div>\n","Shared and Default Prototypes":"\n<h3>Shared Prototype</h3><p>Reuse one Prototype when several Categories need the same Advert attributes and Variant structure. This reduces duplicate setup, mapping differences and Seller training effort.</p>\n<h3>Create another Prototype when</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Product attributes differ materially</li><li>Customer selections differ</li><li>Compliance information differs</li><li>Front-end or integration fields differ</li></ul>\n<h3>Default or No Prototype</h3><p>Use an intentionally blank or minimal Prototype for Categories that only organise the hierarchy. Avoid assigning it to a product Category unless the limited structure is an approved design.</p>\n","Bulk Setup and Structural Changes":"\n<p>Use <code>Categorisation &gt; Prototypes &gt; Bulk Upload</code> after the referenced Option Types and Values exist. Populate the Prototype column for every Category in the Category bulk file.</p>\n<h3>Before changing a live Prototype</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Identify affected Categories, Sellers and products</li><li>Review newly required and removed fields</li><li>Review mappings, V2 workbooks and integrations</li><li>Review Product Vetting, Catalog Rules and front-end filters</li><li>Test product migration in Sandbox</li></ul>\n<p>Category migration requires compatible product structures. Compare source and destination Prototypes before consolidating live Categories.</p>\n","Testing and Governance":"\n<p>Validate each Prototype through manual product creation, V2 bulk workflows and any integrated Seller method.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Test</th><th>Confirm</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Manual product</td><td>Correct Advert, Variant and free-text fields</td></tr><tr><td>V2 workbook</td><td>Correct Category-specific columns and controlled values</td></tr><tr><td>Mapping</td><td>Seller source attributes have approved destinations</td></tr><tr><td>Integration</td><td>Initial creation and later updates remain valid</td></tr><tr><td>Front end</td><td>Product details, Variant selectors and filters work</td></tr><tr><td>Governance</td><td>Catalog Rules and Product Vetting use the intended data</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Maintain a Prototype register containing Categories, attributes, front-end use, integration mapping, owner and environment status.</p>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952526071949-Create-a-prototype\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create a Prototype</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952568064013-Add-a-prototype-to-a-category\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Add a Prototype to a Category</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21949682230285-Create-variants-or-features\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create Variants or Features</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/14556672200205-Manage-optional-option-types\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Optional Option Types</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31709387005709-Updating-categories-and-prototypes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Updating Categories and Prototypes</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["option-types","Option Types"],["categories","Categories"],["bulk-product-management","Bulk Product Management"]]},"categories":{"summary":"Create a clear Category hierarchy, assign a suitable Prototype to every Category and guide Sellers to map source classifications into one consistent marketplace structure.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller management","Ecommerce","Commercial and finance","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understanding Categories":"\n<p>A Category places an Advert within the marketplace taxonomy and helps determine its Prototype, product fields, mapping, reports and Category-specific rules.</p>\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Categories</code></p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Category selected</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Prototype applied</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Seller product fields displayed</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Product mapped and governed</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Connected systems receive classification</strong></div></div>\n<p>The Marketplacer hierarchy can remain operationally stable while the ecommerce platform manages its own menus, Collections and campaign pages.</p>\n","Planning the Category Hierarchy":"\n<p>Design the hierarchy from representative Seller products, operational rules and front-end requirements.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Identify top-level departments</li><li>Identify intermediate grouping Categories</li><li>Identify product Categories</li><li>Confirm the Prototype required by each product type</li><li>Review Seller source Categories and mappings</li><li>Review tax, commission and Catalog Rule dependencies</li></ul>\n<p>Create another level only when it introduces a meaningful product distinction. Use attributes for colour, size, age group, dietary preference, campaigns and temporary merchandising ranges.</p>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Use the most specific appropriate Category.</strong> It is more likely to provide the right Prototype, rules and reporting classification.</div>\n","Creating a Category":"\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Categories &gt; New Category</code></p>\n<ol><li>Enter the Category Name and Title.</li><li>Add useful Alternative Search Terms.</li><li>Select the Parent Category.</li><li>Select the appropriate Prototype.</li><li>Review Brand, condition, tax, purchase-limit and shipping settings.</li><li>Create the Category.</li><li>Verify the complete hierarchy path.</li><li>Test a representative product.</li></ol>\n<p>Create the supporting Option Types, Option Values and Prototypes before large-scale Category creation.</p>\n","Category Settings and Field Reference":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Setting</th><th>Use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Name and Title</td><td>Clear internal and displayed Category labels</td></tr><tr><td>Alternative Search Terms</td><td>Approved synonyms and common search phrases</td></tr><tr><td>Parent</td><td>Position in the hierarchy</td></tr><tr><td>Prototype</td><td>Fields available to products in the Category</td></tr><tr><td>Minimum or maximum purchase quantity</td><td>Shared Category-level purchase controls where supported</td></tr><tr><td>Product tax code</td><td>External tax classification</td></tr><tr><td>Override Sales Tax</td><td>Category-specific rate where approved</td></tr><tr><td>Has Condition</td><td>Allow supported product condition values</td></tr><tr><td>Has Brands</td><td>Allow products to use Brand records</td></tr><tr><td>Parcel defaults</td><td>Approved weight and dimensions where suitable</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Review existing products before disabling Brand or condition support because the change can remove associated product data.</p>\n","Parent, Product and Secondary Categories":"\n<h3>Parent and grouping Categories</h3><p>Use to organise the hierarchy. Assign a blank or minimal Prototype where products are not intended to be listed directly.</p>\n<h3>Product Categories</h3><p>Use a functional Prototype and guide Sellers to assign Adverts at this level.</p>\n<h3>Secondary Categories</h3><p>Use for intentional cross-listing or merchandising where supported, while retaining one authoritative primary Category.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Relationship</th><th>Controls</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Primary Category</td><td>Prototype, main mapping, Category tax, Catalog Rules, reporting and commission matching</td></tr><tr><td>Secondary relationship</td><td>Approved additional discovery or merchandising use</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Front-end Collections are often a better option than adding secondary Category complexity for temporary merchandising.</p>\n","Bulk Setup and Structural Changes":"\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Categories &gt; Bulk Upload</code></p>\n<ol><li>Download the current structure or sample template.</li><li>Retain an unchanged backup.</li><li>Add or update approved rows.</li><li>Populate the Prototype for every Category.</li><li>Validate Parent relationships and field formats.</li><li>Upload the CSV or XLSX file.</li><li>Review import results and failed rows.</li><li>Open representative Categories and generate a product workbook.</li></ol>\n<h3>Live changes</h3><p>Before changing a Prototype, merging Categories or moving products, review mappings, product data, front-end destinations, tax, commission and Catalog Rules. Test the migration in Sandbox.</p>\n","Seller Mapping and Product Assignment":"\n<p>Map Seller source Categories into the approved marketplace hierarchy.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller source</th><th>Marketplace Category</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Technology > Displays > Desktop Screens</td><td>Electronics > Video > Computer Monitors</td></tr><tr><td>Dog Meals</td><td>Animals & Pet Supplies > Pet Supplies > Dog Supplies > Dog Food</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Changing a saved mapping does not necessarily recategorise every existing product. Review and move live Adverts directly where required.</p>\n<h3>V2 product workbooks</h3><p>Selected Categories and assigned Prototypes determine the Category-specific sheets, fields and controlled values in generated product workbooks. Keep system-generated identifiers and hierarchy values unchanged.</p>\n","Testing and Governance":"\n<p>Test each launch Category with single-Variant, multi-Variant, branded, unbranded, integrated and bulk-created products as applicable.</p>\n<h3>Confirm</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Hierarchy and Prototype</li><li>Advert and Variant attributes</li><li>Brand and condition behaviour</li><li>Tax and purchase settings</li><li>Seller mapping</li><li>Front-end destination and filters</li><li>Commission Package and Catalog Rule effects</li><li>Reporting classification</li></ul>\n<p>Maintain a Category register containing the full path, type, Parent, Prototype, tax and commission dependencies, Catalog Rules, front-end destination, owner and status.</p>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115007259468-How-to-set-up-your-categories\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How to Set Up Your Categories</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360054707892-CSV-Bulk-Category-Upload\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">CSV Bulk Category Upload</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952568064013-Add-a-prototype-to-a-category\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Add a Prototype to a Category</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31709387005709-Updating-categories-and-prototypes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Updating Categories and Prototypes</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360042708032-Configure-Alternative-search-terms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Configure Alternative Search Terms</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003511551-Map-product-categories-brands-features-and-variants\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Map Product Categories, Brands, Features and Variants</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/39514847581709-Search-Adverts-in-the-Operator-portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Search Adverts in the Operator Portal</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["prototypes","Prototypes"],["mapping","Mapping"],["catalog-rules","Catalog Rules"]]},"brands":{"summary":"Create and maintain one controlled Brand list, prevent duplicate records and map Seller source values to the approved marketplace Brand used by products, commercial rules and connected systems.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller management","Ecommerce","Commercial teams","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understanding Brands":"\n<p>A Brand identifies the manufacturer or commercial label associated with an Advert. It is separate from the Seller supplying the product.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Record</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller</td><td>Example Electronics Retailer</td></tr><tr><td>Product Brand</td><td>Samsung</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Brands</code></p>\n<p>One controlled Brand record supports product mapping, filters, reporting, Commission Package Brand rules and Golden Product workflows.</p>\n","Planning Brand Standards":"\n<p>Collect launch Seller Brand lists and resolve aliases, duplicates, private labels, unbranded products and restricted Brands before loading the catalogue.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller source</th><th>Marketplace Brand</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Samsung Electronics Co.</td><td>Samsung</td></tr><tr><td>SAMSUNG</td><td>Samsung</td></tr><tr><td>The Northface</td><td>The North Face</td></tr><tr><td>Apple Inc.</td><td>Apple</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Use the approved public Brand name</li><li>Preserve intentional Brand styling and capitalisation</li><li>Separate parent companies from true product Brands</li><li>Create private-label Brands where they represent the product identity</li><li>Use one approved Unbranded or Generic value</li></ul>\n","Creating and Editing Brands":"\n<ol><li>Search <code>Categorisation &gt; Brands</code> for an existing equivalent.</li><li>Select <strong>New Brand</strong>.</li><li>Enter the approved Brand name.</li><li>Review <strong>Show in Advert Title</strong>.</li><li>Add supported Brand information such as a size chart where appropriate.</li><li>Save and test the Brand through product creation or mapping.</li></ol>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Review title behaviour.</strong> Enabling Brand insertion where Seller titles already contain the Brand can produce duplicate wording.</div>\n<p>Before renaming a live Brand, review products, mappings, Commission Packages, front-end filters, size charts, reports and Golden Products.</p>\n","Bulk Upload and Catalogue Updates":"\n<p>Use <code>Categorisation &gt; Brands &gt; Bulk upload</code> for several approved Brands.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Required column</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Name</td><td>Approved marketplace Brand</td></tr><tr><td>Show in Advert Title</td><td>Controls supported title behaviour</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Validate duplicate names, capitalisation, Seller names used incorrectly as Brands, private labels, restrictions and title settings.</p>\n<h3>Product updates</h3><p>Use the current V2 Seller or Operator product-management workflow to correct Brand assignments. Match the marketplace Brand exactly and retain Advert identifiers during updates.</p>\n","Category and Product Requirements":"\n<p>Brands can be assigned only where the product Category supports them.</p>\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Categories &gt; edit Category &gt; Has Brands</code></p>\n<p>Enable Brands where products are commonly identified by a manufacturer or label. Review existing catalogue and connected-system impact before disabling the setting because associated Brand values can be removed from affected Adverts.</p>\n<h3>Seller guidance</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Approved Brand list</li><li>Unbranded standard</li><li>New Brand request process</li><li>Restricted Brand policy</li><li>Exact naming and mapping instructions</li></ul>\n","Seller Mapping and Brand Requests":"\n<p>Map Seller source Brands to existing marketplace Brands whenever the values represent the same label.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller source</th><th>Marketplace</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Samsung Electronics</td><td>Samsung</td></tr><tr><td>NorthFace</td><td>The North Face</td></tr><tr><td>APPLE</td><td>Apple</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>When the Brand is missing</h3><ol><li>Review the source value and product evidence.</li><li>Search for aliases or existing equivalents.</li><li>Approve, reject, restrict or map to an existing Brand according to marketplace policy.</li><li>Create the Brand where approved.</li><li>Save the Seller mapping.</li><li>Verify affected and future product imports.</li></ol>\n<p>Prioritise requests affecting the largest number of products and maintain an audit trail for restricted Brands.</p>\n","Front-End and Integration Behaviour":"\n<p>Define where the Marketplacer Brand is stored in each connected system.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Marketplacer</th><th>Possible destination</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Brand</td><td>Native Brand or manufacturer field</td></tr><tr><td>Brand</td><td>Vendor field</td></tr><tr><td>Brand</td><td>Tag or metafield</td></tr><tr><td>Brand</td><td>Search-filter attribute</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Confirm product-page display, filtering, title transformation, product feeds, updates and removals. For platforms without a native Brand field, agree the alternative with the integration team.</p>\n<h3>Commercial dependency</h3><p>Review Brand-based Commission Package rules before renaming, consolidating or remapping a Brand. An incorrect assignment can change commission on new Orders.</p>\n","Testing and Governance":"\n<p>Test exact matches, aliases, missing Brands, approved requests, restricted Brands, V2 product files and full catalogue resynchronisation.</p>\n<h3>Brand audit</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Duplicate and alternate spelling</li><li>Brands with no products</li><li>Seller names used as Brands</li><li>Incorrect Unbranded use</li><li>Pending and restricted requests</li><li>Incorrect mappings</li><li>Commission discrepancies</li><li>Outdated size charts</li></ul>\n<p>Maintain a Brand register containing aliases, Category scope, title behaviour, front-end destination, commercial dependencies, restriction status, owner and review date.</p>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360003494972-Import-new-brands-in-bulk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Import New Brands in Bulk</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/46847697430029-Brand-mapping-overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Brand Mapping Overview</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/46847743863309-How-to-manage-brand-mapping-in-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Brand Mapping in the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115007259468-How-to-set-up-your-categories\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How to Set Up Your Categories</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003511551-Map-product-categories-brands-features-and-variants\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Map Product Categories, Brands, Features and Variants</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/39486165269645-Bulk-product-management-overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bulk Product Management Overview</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["mapping","Mapping"],["commission-packages","Commission Packages"],["golden-records","Golden Records and Central Product Database"]]},"setup-sequence":{"summary":"Build the marketplace taxonomy in an order that respects dependencies, validate representative Seller products in Sandbox and apply the approved structure in Production.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Seller management","Ecommerce","Commercial and finance","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understanding the Setup Sequence":"\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Confirm scope and taxonomy approach</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Create Option Types</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Add Option Values</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Create Prototypes</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Create Categories</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Create Brands</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Test Seller products and mappings</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">8</span><strong>Apply in Production</strong></div></div>\n<p>The sequence is operational guidance rather than a strict technical limitation for every component. It reduces rework by making each dependency available before it is used.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Global Taxonomy implementations use the same review order.</strong> Review existing Option Types, Values, Prototypes and Categories before onboarding products.</div>\n","Define the Scope and Design":"\n<h3>Collect representative data</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Seller Category paths</li><li>Product titles and Brands</li><li>Advert attributes</li><li>Variant options and values</li><li>SKUs and product volume</li><li>Source systems</li><li>Tax and compliance information</li></ul>\n<h3>Confirm the approach</h3><p>Choose the complete Global Taxonomy, an approved subset, the standard with targeted additions or a custom industry structure.</p>\n<h3>Create a taxonomy workbook</h3><p>Record Category, Prototype, Advert and Variant Option Types, Option Values, Brand requirements, front-end destination, Seller sources, financial dependencies, owner and status.</p>\n","Create Option Types and Option Values":"\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Option Types</code></p>\n<ol><li>Create Advert and Variant Option Types.</li><li>Set clear Name, Presentation, Description, Kind and input behaviour.</li><li>Confirm required or optional status.</li><li>Add approved controlled Option Values.</li><li>Apply consistent units, spelling and order.</li><li>Test mapping of representative Seller values.</li></ol>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Separate descriptive and selectable data.</strong> Advert attributes describe the product. Variant attributes distinguish the purchasable items.</div>\n","Build Prototypes":"\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Prototypes</code></p>\n<ol><li>Create product-specific or approved shared Prototypes.</li><li>Add the required Advert Option Types.</li><li>Add customer-selectable Variant Option Types.</li><li>Add supported free-text fields where needed.</li><li>Create a blank or minimal grouping Prototype.</li><li>Test a representative product model.</li></ol>\n<p>Keep each Prototype focused on the fields relevant to its product type and confirm all required Option Values exist.</p>\n","Create Categories and Brands":"\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Categories</code></p><p>Create parent Categories before child Categories and assign a Prototype to every Category.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Category type</th><th>Prototype</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Grouping Category</td><td>Default, No Prototype or approved minimal Prototype</td></tr><tr><td>Product Category</td><td>Functional product-specific or shared Prototype</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><code>Categorisation &gt; Brands</code></p><p>Create or bulk upload the approved Brand list after naming, Unbranded, private-label and restricted Brand standards are confirmed.</p>\n","Validate Seller Product Workflows":"\n<p>The taxonomy is ready when real Seller products can complete the intended onboarding journey.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Workflow</th><th>Test</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Manual product creation</td><td>Category selection, fields, Brand and unique Variants</td></tr><tr><td>V2 Multi Sheet</td><td>Category-based creation and controlled dropdowns</td></tr><tr><td>V2 Single Sheet</td><td>High-volume creation and updates using reference data</td></tr><tr><td>Seller mapping</td><td>Category, Brand, Option Type and Option Value transformations</td></tr><tr><td>MConnect or API</td><td>Initial import, updates, missing values and resynchronisation</td></tr><tr><td>Front end</td><td>Product detail, Variant selectors, filters and Collections</td></tr><tr><td>Governance</td><td>Catalog Rules, Product Vetting, tax and commission</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Use a controlled group of representative Sellers before scaling to the full launch catalogue.</p>\n","Apply the Structure in Production":"\n<p>Retain the approved taxonomy workbook, bulk files, mapping register, front-end mapping, test evidence and approval record.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Option Types</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Option Values</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Prototypes</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Categories</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Brands</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Seller mappings</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Production smoke test</strong></div></div>\n<h3>Compare environments</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Component counts</li><li>Category hierarchy</li><li>Prototype assignments</li><li>Required and optional attributes</li><li>Option Values and Brands</li><li>Tax and Category settings</li><li>Front-end and integration mapping</li></ul>\n<p>Use one controlled Seller and product for the Production smoke test before broader onboarding.</p>\n","Governance and Readiness":"\n<h3>Assign ownership</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Taxonomy strategy</li><li>Option Types and Values</li><li>Prototypes and Categories</li><li>Brands and Seller mappings</li><li>Front-end and integration mapping</li><li>Tax and commission review</li><li>Production approval</li></ul>\n<h3>Establish request processes</h3><p>Define how teams request new Categories, Brands, Option Types, Option Values and Prototype changes. Search the existing structure and assess dependencies before creating another record.</p>\n<h3>Readiness</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Launch scope and standards approved</li><li>Sandbox workflows passed</li><li>Production structure compared</li><li>Seller resources prepared</li><li>Change register and owners assigned</li><li>Ongoing catalogue review scheduled</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/27901303371533-Marketplacer-Global-Taxonomy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Marketplacer Global Taxonomy</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21949682230285-Create-variants-or-features\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create Variants or Features</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952355396749-Add-option-values-to-variants-or-features\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Add Option Values to Variants or Features</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952526071949-Create-a-prototype\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create a Prototype</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/21952568064013-Add-a-prototype-to-a-category\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Add a Prototype to a Category</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115007259468-How-to-set-up-your-categories\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">How to Set Up Your Categories</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360003494972-Import-new-brands-in-bulk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Import New Brands in Bulk</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31709387005709-Updating-categories-and-prototypes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Updating Categories and Prototypes</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["understanding-taxonomy","Understanding Taxonomy"],["bulk-product-management","Bulk Product Management"],["configuration-testing","Marketplace Configuration Testing"]]}};
